title: Matador Cup live scores: Tasmania v WA live blog from Drummoyne Oval
text:
MITCHELL Johnson came back with a bang in today’s Matador Cup clash between Western Australia and Tasmania.
Australia’s pace spearhead hadn’t played a competitive match since the end of the Ashes series so was itching to make an impact, and after waiting for Warriors teammates Joel Paris and Nathan Coulter-Nile to bowl the first few overs, Johnson was unleashed on Tigers batsmen Dom Michael and Ben Dunk in the seventh over.
The left-armer went for nine runs in his opening over, hit for two boundaries, one of which was off a free hit that saw Michael play a one-handed cover drive while down on one knee.
There was more drama in Johnson’s next over as he once again bowled a no-ball, with Dunk caught off the subsequent free hit.
Dunk was eventually out for 51, bowled by Adam Voges to leave Tasmania on 9-222 after 50 overs at Drummoyne Oval.
Get the latest updates in our live blog below.
 Live: Mixed bag from Johnson in comeback
